               <msContents>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Ostracon, fragment (two fragments - the smaller one comprising three pieces) of the body of a brown pottery ribbed vessel, the fabric is partially grey in section, the interior is covered with a dark-brown resinous deposit, exterior covered with a red-brown slip and remains of sixteen lines of Coptic text written in black ink, worn and smudged in places, the smaller fragment has remains of nine of the lines of text, containing an account of wine.</note>
